- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses security vulnerabilities and proposes a solution to address them. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses a hardware feature and its software implementation. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is relevant as the paper proposes a software abstraction for a hardware feature. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the compatibility of MPK with mprotect() and proposes a solution to address the semantic-gap problem. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a software solution to address scalability and compatibility issues.
